#MEM id=rules source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/mia/skills/design-and-build/vercel-react-best-practices/rules/rerender-memo-with-default-value.md savings=16%
M||tx|---
M||titl|Extract Default Non-primitive Parameter Value from Memoized cp to Constant
M||impa|md
M||impa|restores memoization by using a constant for default value
M||tags|rerender, memo, op
M||tx|---
M|Extr|tx|When memoized cp has a default value for some non-primitive optional parameter, such as an array, fn, or object, calling the cp w/o that parameter results in broken memoization. This is bc new value instances are created on every rerender, and they do not pass strict equality comparison in `memo()`.
M|Extr|tx|To address this issue, extract the default value into a constant.
M|Extr|**In|**
M|Extr|tx|```tsx
M|Extr|cons|{ onClick?: () => void }) {
M|Extr|tx|// ...
M|Extr|tx|})
M|Extr|tx|// Used w/o optional onClick
M|Extr|tx|<UserAvatar />
M|Extr|tx|```
M|Extr|**Co|**
M|Extr|tx|```tsx
M|Extr|tx|const NOOP = () => {};
M|Extr|cons|{ onClick?: () => void }) {
M|Extr|tx|// ...
M|Extr|tx|})
M|Extr|tx|// Used w/o optional onClick
M|Extr|tx|<UserAvatar />
M|Extr|tx|```